{
  "texts": [
    "In the commercial field, the design and implementation of HRI systems must consider a diverse range of factors specific to the application environment.",
    "To improve the collection of brain signals, it is crucial to develop high signal-to-noise ratio data collection and transfer systems.",
    "Portable, noise-insensitive, and comfortable headset systems are required to ensure relatively pure brain activity is captured for long-term use.",
    "Effective decoding systems require ideal analysis algorithms that can achieve fast and accurate signal processing and information transfer.",
    "Despite the limitations of BCI-based HRI, its potential to enhance human-robot collaboration and increase productivity in various industries such as manufacturing, healthcare, and logistics is significant."
  ]
}